01:39.273 --> 01:40.491
Well...

01:40.578 --> 01:42.014
why didn't you
call for help?

01:42.102 --> 01:43.407
I did.

01:43.494 --> 01:45.453
I threw fruit.

01:45.540 --> 01:48.499
Oh, God, maybe we should get
you to the emergency room.

01:48.586 --> 01:49.979
Oh, it's just a sprain.

01:50.066 --> 01:51.372
Let me see.

01:51.459 --> 01:53.896
Wrong leg, wrong leg,
wrong leg!

02:09.520 --> 02:10.782
[groans softly]

02:10.869 --> 02:12.741
These cookie are wet, Mom.

02:13.785 --> 02:15.265
I'm sorry.

02:18.225 --> 02:19.139
Are you crazy?

02:19.226 --> 02:20.314
Get off that foot.

02:20.401 --> 02:22.316
Let me put the groceries away.

02:22.403 --> 02:23.839
[sighs]
No.

02:23.926 --> 02:25.101
If you do it, I'll
never find anything.

02:25.188 --> 02:27.408
You've got two cabinets.

02:27.495 --> 02:29.236
It's not exactly
a scavenger hunt.

02:30.628 --> 02:31.673
I got this.

02:31.760 --> 02:32.848
All right, fine.

02:32.935 --> 02:34.502
At least tell me why

02:34.589 --> 02:35.590
you won't let a doctor
look at your ankle.

02:35.677 --> 02:36.808
[sighs]

02:36.895 --> 02:38.375
Because he might say it's broken

02:38.462 --> 02:40.508
and I don't have time for that.

02:40.595 --> 02:41.639
[clicks tongue]

02:41.726 --> 02:43.119
Oh, yeah.
Good strategy.

02:43.206 --> 02:46.035
Is it your plan
to tough out the roof, too?

02:46.122 --> 02:47.254
[Christy sighs]

02:47.341 --> 02:48.472
I called the
landlord

02:48.559 --> 02:50.518
over and over.

02:50.605 --> 02:51.171
Each time,
his English got worse.

02:53.260 --> 02:54.522
VIOLET:
Mom! Grandma!

02:54.609 --> 02:56.176
Get in here!
The baby's moving!

02:56.263 --> 02:57.438
[gasps]

02:57.525 --> 02:58.308
I'm coming! Ow.

02:58.395 --> 02:59.440
I'm coming! Ow.

02:59.527 --> 03:01.224
CHRISTY:
I'm coming. Ow.

03:01.311 --> 03:02.443
Oh, my God.
There it is!

03:02.530 --> 03:03.531
Right?
[laughs]

03:03.618 --> 03:04.880
Let me feel! Let me feel!

03:04.967 --> 03:06.186
Ow. Ah, where?

03:06.273 --> 03:07.230
Where?

03:09.319 --> 03:10.059
Guess it stopped.

03:12.148 --> 03:13.149
Wait.

03:14.629 --> 03:15.673
Nope, just gas.

03:17.893 --> 03:19.460
I gotta call Luke.

03:21.897 --> 03:22.898
[groans]

03:25.161 --> 03:26.858
Don't feel bad.

03:26.945 --> 03:28.469
You'll have plenty of time
to spend with that baby

03:28.556 --> 03:29.861
after Violet dumps it on you.

03:31.733 --> 03:32.864
Thanks, Mom.

03:32.951 --> 03:33.735
It's funny...

03:33.822 --> 03:35.215
'cause it's true.

03:47.183 --> 03:50.708
It was so smart
to keep this walking boot.

03:50.795 --> 03:52.232
How'd you hurt your ankle
the last time?

03:52.319 --> 03:55.147
Oh, you know...

03:55.235 --> 03:56.801
back when I was drinking,

03:56.888 --> 03:58.238
I had this pesky habit

03:58.325 --> 04:00.022
of slipping on my own vomit.

04:00.109 --> 04:02.111
A tale as old as time.

04:03.330 --> 04:05.549
[sighs]

04:05.636 --> 04:08.117
Please tell me you
microwaved that sponge

04:08.204 --> 04:09.205
before you did the dishes.

04:09.292 --> 04:10.902
What? Why?

04:10.989 --> 04:12.556
To kill the germs.

04:12.643 --> 04:14.254
You're serious?

04:14.341 --> 04:16.865
This thing is filled
with bacteria.

04:16.952 --> 04:20.260
Might as well be washing dishes
in the toilet.

04:20.346 --> 04:22.043
Wow.

04:22.130 --> 04:23.785
What happened to
the fun-lovin' chick

04:23.872 --> 04:26.135
who liked to slip and slide
through her own vomit?

04:26.222 --> 04:29.094
She watched a very scary exposé
on the 6:00 news

04:29.181 --> 04:30.966
about how your kitchen
can kill you

04:31.053 --> 04:32.184
and everyone you love.

04:34.230 --> 04:36.754
Somebody really needs
to get laid.

04:37.842 --> 04:39.191
I can hear you, Mom.

04:39.279 --> 04:40.149
You were meant to.

04:40.236 --> 04:42.194
By the way, it's gonna

04:42.282 --> 04:43.674
rain again in
a couple of days.

04:43.761 --> 04:44.719
What do you want
to do about the leak?

04:44.806 --> 04:46.329
I don't know.

04:46.416 --> 04:48.940
If I could figure out
where the hole was,

04:49.027 --> 04:50.551
I'd probably jab
a tampon in it.

04:52.857 --> 04:54.555
Nice.

04:54.642 --> 04:56.383
That way, the house can do
archery and ride a horse.

04:58.428 --> 04:59.386
I guess I'll just

04:59.473 --> 05:00.778
climb up there

05:00.865 --> 05:02.214
and throw a big tarp
over everything.

05:02.302 --> 05:03.868
Really?
With one foot?

05:03.955 --> 05:06.044
Who else is gonna do it, Mom?

05:06.131 --> 05:07.655
Are you gonna do it?

05:07.742 --> 05:09.309
You don't even know
to microwave a sponge.

05:11.876 --> 05:13.051
Why don't you just call Baxter

05:13.138 --> 05:14.879
and see if he can fix it?Ah!

05:14.966 --> 05:16.359
My ex-husband?

05:16.446 --> 05:18.318
You want to send
a stoner up to the roof

05:18.405 --> 05:21.059
with hot tar and a nail gun.

05:21.146 --> 05:23.192
How's that not gonna
end in tears?

05:25.890 --> 05:27.196
Well, I'm calling him.

05:27.283 --> 05:29.241
Maybe you
should get laid.

05:29.329 --> 05:31.766
I did.

05:33.637 --> 05:35.900
Might want to microwave
your sheets.

05:41.384 --> 05:43.560
Whoa.

05:43.647 --> 05:44.996
What's the matter?

05:45.083 --> 05:46.607
I felt the baby move.

05:46.694 --> 05:47.869
Ah!

05:47.956 --> 05:48.826
The baby's moving!

05:48.913 --> 05:50.524
Violet, I'm coming!

05:50.611 --> 05:51.307
I'm coming!

05:51.394 --> 05:53.875
I'm coming.

05:53.962 --> 05:55.920
Shake your belly!
Keep it moving!

05:58.445 --> 06:00.403
[microwave beeps]

06:07.671 --> 06:09.630
I always wondered
how they made sponges.

06:15.418 --> 06:16.332
[knocking at door]

06:16.419 --> 06:17.377
[door opens]

06:21.555 --> 06:23.470
Somebody need a hole plugged?

06:25.602 --> 06:27.822
Oh, God.

06:28.910 --> 06:30.128
There's a...

06:30.215 --> 06:31.782
old tarp in the shed.

06:31.869 --> 06:34.089
Just cover as much
of the roof as you can,

06:34.176 --> 06:35.264
and I'll get a roofer
out here next week.

06:35.351 --> 06:36.352
A roofer?

06:36.439 --> 06:37.353
[laughs]

06:37.440 --> 06:38.572
La-di-dah!

06:38.659 --> 06:41.270
When did you get
so middle-class?

06:43.228 --> 06:44.926
Can you find the leak,

06:45.013 --> 06:47.145
cover it with hot tar,
and then reshingle?

06:47.232 --> 06:50.627
There's a couple of steps
I didn't know about, but yeah.

06:52.412 --> 06:53.891
What happened
to your paw?

06:53.978 --> 06:55.632
Oh... I fell.

06:55.719 --> 06:57.199
Were you loaded?

06:57.286 --> 06:59.331
No.

06:59.419 --> 07:01.421
That's where you went wrong.

07:02.509 --> 07:04.206
Never fall sober.

07:04.293 --> 07:05.425
You tense up.

07:06.513 --> 07:07.427
Thanks for the tip.

07:07.514 --> 07:09.603
It's a scientific fact.

07:09.690 --> 07:10.995
You can't get hurt
when you're high.

07:12.910 --> 07:15.609
I don't make the rules.

07:18.176 --> 07:20.135
[beer can popping open]

07:23.704 --> 07:25.227
Mr. Baxter...

07:25.314 --> 07:27.621
Oh!

07:27.708 --> 07:29.623
That was my only beer!

07:29.710 --> 07:31.973
Sorry.

07:32.060 --> 07:33.148
I got weed.

07:33.235 --> 07:34.454
Forgiven.

07:37.108 --> 07:39.676
Need any help?You know how to patch
a leaky roof?

07:39.763 --> 07:42.374
No.That makes two of us.

07:42.462 --> 07:44.202
Here, let's just
rip up shingles,

07:44.289 --> 07:45.508
and if we see
the living room,

07:45.595 --> 07:47.554
we've gone too far.

07:50.121 --> 07:52.820
I once patched a leak
in a swimming pool.

07:52.907 --> 07:54.038
Yeah?
How'd that go?

07:54.125 --> 07:55.649
Not good.

07:55.736 --> 07:58.347
Apparently, you gotta
take the water out first.

07:58.434 --> 07:59.827
Hey, can I ask you a question?

07:59.914 --> 08:03.483
The capital of Ethiopia
is Addis Ababa.

08:03.570 --> 08:05.615
What?

08:05.702 --> 08:09.097
That's just something
I like that I know.

08:09.184 --> 08:11.142
No one ever asks.

08:11.229 --> 08:13.362
Actually, I was gonna
ask you about having a baby.

08:13.449 --> 08:15.059
Oh.

08:15.146 --> 08:16.626
Yeah, you don't want
to have one of those

08:16.713 --> 08:17.975
until you're,
like, 45, 50

08:18.062 --> 08:19.673
and you can't have
any more fun

08:19.760 --> 08:21.022
or your heart'll
explode.

08:22.589 --> 08:23.981
No, dude,

08:24.068 --> 08:26.114
Violet's having
my baby in a few months.

08:26.201 --> 08:27.985
Oh...

08:28.072 --> 08:29.509
Well, game over.

08:32.207 --> 08:33.600
It's starting to kick.

08:33.687 --> 08:34.775
Oh, that's big.

08:34.861 --> 08:37.778
Yeah. It's really happening.

08:37.865 --> 08:40.171
I just don't know
if I'm ready to be a dad.

08:40.258 --> 08:40.998
[laughs]

08:41.085 --> 08:42.565
Been there.

08:42.652 --> 08:43.914
Really?

08:44.001 --> 08:45.394
Yeah, absolutely.

08:45.481 --> 08:47.091
Believe it or not,
I had grave doubts

08:47.178 --> 08:48.919
about my own
parenting abilities.

08:49.006 --> 08:51.095
I just don't want
to turn into my father.

08:51.182 --> 08:53.707
I mean, I love him, but...
you'd only give him

08:53.794 --> 08:57.014
a "world's greatest dad"
T-shirt ironically.

08:57.101 --> 08:58.146
Yeah.

08:58.233 --> 08:59.843
I had a father like that.

08:59.930 --> 09:02.498
Vice cop in Oakland.

09:02.585 --> 09:04.544
I sure showed him.

09:06.807 --> 09:09.157
Let me tell you something:
When the baby gets here,

09:09.244 --> 09:10.419
you'll know what to do.

09:10.506 --> 09:11.463
I hope so.

09:11.551 --> 09:12.639
I'll never forget

09:12.726 --> 09:14.641
driving home from the hospital

09:14.728 --> 09:16.556
after Roscoe was born.

09:16.643 --> 09:18.427
I looked in the rearview mirror
at him in his car seat,

09:18.514 --> 09:19.515
and I just...
knew I could do it.

09:19.602 --> 09:21.909
Cool.

09:21.996 --> 09:23.650
Yeah.

09:23.737 --> 09:26.304
If Christy hadn't caught me
banging her best friend,

09:26.391 --> 09:27.958
I'd still be doing it.

09:29.481 --> 09:30.700
Don't worry.

09:30.787 --> 09:31.919
You'll be a great dad.

09:32.006 --> 09:33.355
Thanks.

09:33.442 --> 09:35.096
It sounds like
you're a great dad, too.

09:35.183 --> 09:36.663
[laughs]

09:36.750 --> 09:38.316
I do my best.

09:38.403 --> 09:40.623
Now, let's smoke that weed
before I go crazy.

09:44.540 --> 09:46.760
[Baxter and Luke laughing]

09:49.632 --> 09:52.635
It sounds like Luke and Baxter
are getting along.

09:53.723 --> 09:55.682
I know that laugh.

09:58.510 --> 09:59.511
They're getting ready
to order pizza.

10:04.560 --> 10:05.909
Just my luck.

10:05.996 --> 10:08.303
I got a couple of
idiot nine-year-olds

10:08.390 --> 10:09.609
fixing my roof.

10:09.696 --> 10:12.002
I'm nine.

10:13.569 --> 10:15.571
Nothing to brag about.

10:15.658 --> 10:17.660
BAXTER:
Hey, man, let's order a pizza!

10:24.928 --> 10:25.886
Ow!

10:29.237 --> 10:30.238
Ow!

10:34.459 --> 10:35.635
Ah!

10:36.679 --> 10:37.549
This is fun.

10:41.553 --> 10:42.903
What are you doing?

10:42.990 --> 10:43.555
Working.

10:45.601 --> 10:47.516
I knew I should've
handled this myself.

10:47.603 --> 10:50.345
Christy, it's done.

10:50.432 --> 10:52.086
Look. All sealed.

10:52.173 --> 10:53.478
Just got to let it dry

10:53.565 --> 10:55.132
and put the shingles
on tomorrow.

10:55.219 --> 10:57.047
Oh.

10:57.134 --> 10:58.266
Okay.

10:58.353 --> 11:00.094
Good.

11:00.181 --> 11:02.444
Just promise me
you'll be careful.

11:02.531 --> 11:03.619
Promise.

11:03.706 --> 11:05.186
I don't care if you get high.

11:05.273 --> 11:07.057
I just don't want anybody
getting hurt.

11:07.144 --> 11:09.669
We are not getting high.

11:13.107 --> 11:14.630
She knows, dude.

11:16.980 --> 11:18.721
Relax.
We're being real safe.

11:18.808 --> 11:21.332
Thank you.

11:21.419 --> 11:23.073
No, no, no, no, no!

11:23.160 --> 11:24.161
[crashing]

11:27.121 --> 11:29.471
Oh. She tensed up.

11:37.697 --> 11:40.700
It was so smart
to save this.

11:43.180 --> 11:44.921
Another vomit-related injury?

11:45.008 --> 11:46.401
[sighs]

11:46.488 --> 11:47.445
No.

11:47.532 --> 11:48.577
Slammed it in a car door.

11:48.664 --> 11:50.057
Drunk?Acid.

11:50.144 --> 11:51.319
Ah.

11:51.406 --> 11:54.409
Thought I was invisible.

11:54.496 --> 11:57.151
[sighs] I can't believe
you're going to work.

11:57.238 --> 11:58.630
Why not?

11:58.718 --> 11:59.980
Your ankle's the size
of a grapefruit.

12:00.067 --> 12:02.069
You just fell off
a freaking ladder.

12:02.156 --> 12:03.548
It's a miracle you're not
driving a wheelchair

12:03.635 --> 12:05.159
with your tongue.

12:05.246 --> 12:07.074
I'm fine.

12:07.161 --> 12:08.553
It's just a sprain...

12:12.993 --> 12:14.298
What are you
trying to prove?

12:14.385 --> 12:15.038
[sighs]

12:15.125 --> 12:15.865
Nothing.

12:15.952 --> 12:18.563
I have a job.

12:18.650 --> 12:20.522
I've got bills,
I've got obligations...

12:20.609 --> 12:21.871
[keys clatter to floor]

12:24.134 --> 12:25.745
Would you like me
to pick that up for you?

12:26.789 --> 12:28.878
No. Thank you.

12:46.591 --> 12:49.246
Oh...

12:51.509 --> 12:53.120
Got it!

12:56.601 --> 12:58.647
Soup's up.

12:58.734 --> 13:00.954
Oh, God.

13:01.041 --> 13:02.607
Not more soup.

13:02.694 --> 13:05.567
Careful.

13:05.654 --> 13:07.525
Very hot.

13:09.571 --> 13:10.746
I'll see you in hell.

13:13.227 --> 13:14.750
[gasps]

13:14.837 --> 13:15.751
Ah...

13:15.838 --> 13:16.883
Ow.

13:16.970 --> 13:18.362
Ow, ow, ow, ow.

13:18.449 --> 13:20.756
Ow, ow, ow.

13:20.843 --> 13:21.757
Ow, ow, ow.

13:21.844 --> 13:23.019
Ow.

13:23.106 --> 13:24.934
Why is this
so enjoyable?

13:25.021 --> 13:28.416
I think 'cause
we're bad people.

13:29.939 --> 13:31.898
[gasps]

13:32.942 --> 13:34.639
Son of a bitch.

13:36.772 --> 13:38.513
Hot, hot, hot, hot.

13:38.600 --> 13:39.166
Hot, hot, hot.

13:39.253 --> 13:41.690
Ah, hot.

13:41.777 --> 13:43.953
Ah... hot.

13:44.040 --> 13:44.954
Ah...

13:45.041 --> 13:45.607
ah... ah...

13:45.694 --> 13:47.609
[panting]

13:47.696 --> 13:48.697
Ah...

13:50.786 --> 13:51.743
Ah... ooh...

13:51.831 --> 13:53.833
[panting]

13:57.967 --> 14:00.709
Uh...

14:00.796 --> 14:03.930
It appears we are
out of soup.

14:18.727 --> 14:19.641
Mmm.

14:19.728 --> 14:21.034
[door closes]

14:21.121 --> 14:22.078
What are you doing
back so early?

14:22.165 --> 14:23.993
Oh...

14:24.080 --> 14:26.039
Gabriel sent me home.

14:26.126 --> 14:26.604
He didn't fire you,
did he?

14:26.691 --> 14:29.303
No.

14:29.390 --> 14:31.566
The one perk to having slept
with your married boss

14:31.653 --> 14:33.655
is job security.

14:36.266 --> 14:37.702
Why don't you relax
and I'll make dinner?

14:37.789 --> 14:38.965
No, I got it.

14:39.052 --> 14:41.054
Christy...I said I got it!

14:48.539 --> 14:52.500
[sobbing loudly]

14:52.587 --> 14:54.415
[sobbing]:
I don't got it.

14:54.502 --> 14:56.199
[Christy sniffs]

14:56.286 --> 14:57.722
I don't got it.

14:57.809 --> 14:59.333
What's that I hear?

14:59.420 --> 15:01.030
Was that a cry for help?

15:03.903 --> 15:05.905
I'm done.

15:06.906 --> 15:08.820
There's nothing left.

15:08.908 --> 15:11.475
[sniffs]

15:11.562 --> 15:14.043
I still didn't hear
the word "help."

15:18.743 --> 15:19.962
Help.

15:24.749 --> 15:26.751
[sobbing]Oh...

15:28.753 --> 15:29.885
Come here.

15:29.972 --> 15:31.191
Let's get you into bed,

15:31.278 --> 15:32.670
and I will cook us all
a nice dinner.

15:32.757 --> 15:34.803
Thank you.

15:34.890 --> 15:35.891
[sniffs]

15:38.024 --> 15:39.939
How do you feel
about some hot soup?

15:44.856 --> 15:47.381
Thanks for helping out, man.

15:47.468 --> 15:48.991
My pleasure.

15:49.078 --> 15:50.645
Pitching in around here
makes me feel better

15:50.732 --> 15:53.822
about being late with
the child support payments.

15:53.909 --> 15:56.303
You'll understand
that soon enough.

15:59.045 --> 16:00.350
I really appreciate
you talking me

16:00.437 --> 16:01.308
through this whole
baby thing.

16:01.395 --> 16:03.179
Ah, it was nothing.

16:03.266 --> 16:05.007
No, man, it was
a big help.

16:05.094 --> 16:06.704
I would give you

16:06.791 --> 16:09.403
a "world's greatest dad"
T-shirt unironically.

16:12.493 --> 16:15.975
Wow. Thanks.

16:16.062 --> 16:18.194
I don't get a lot of
positive feedback.

16:19.848 --> 16:22.024
All right.

16:22.111 --> 16:23.025
Enough emotion.

16:23.112 --> 16:24.331
Let's get baked.

16:24.418 --> 16:26.681
Right.

16:28.378 --> 16:30.206
I'm just so tired.

16:30.293 --> 16:32.426
That's because you don't
let anybody help you.

16:32.513 --> 16:33.862
[sighs]
I would,

16:33.949 --> 16:35.385
but then things
don't get done right.

16:35.472 --> 16:38.084
Before you know it,
everything's falling apart.

16:38.171 --> 16:40.477
Stop tucking.
I'm not a burrito.

16:41.696 --> 16:43.219
Sorry.

16:43.306 --> 16:44.090
And you don't know how
to fluff a pillow.

16:44.177 --> 16:46.005
Oh, go fluff yourself.

16:48.224 --> 16:49.138
Sure.

16:49.225 --> 16:50.357
Abandon me.

16:50.444 --> 16:51.532
That's how this all started.

16:51.619 --> 16:53.055
Come again?

16:53.142 --> 16:54.709
Forget it.

16:54.796 --> 16:56.276
No, you-you seriously think

16:56.363 --> 16:57.016
I'm the reason
you're a control freak?

16:59.061 --> 17:00.236
You seriously don't?

17:00.323 --> 17:02.195
Here we go.

17:02.282 --> 17:05.762
Welcome back to another exciting
episode of Blaming Bonnie!

17:05.849 --> 17:07.765
As far back as I can remember,

17:07.852 --> 17:08.896
I came home every night
to an empty house.

17:08.983 --> 17:12.291
Ah, I've seen this one.

17:12.378 --> 17:13.902
If I didn't cook dinner,
I didn't eat.

17:13.989 --> 17:15.512
At least the fridge
was filled with food.

17:15.598 --> 17:17.079
Don't you dare defend yourself!

17:17.165 --> 17:18.602
But I provided. I...No, no, no, no, no! No!

17:18.689 --> 17:20.517
This is not a conversation.

17:20.604 --> 17:22.258
Do I have
to remind you

17:22.345 --> 17:23.390
that I raised myself?

17:23.477 --> 17:25.521
I did my own
laundry,

17:25.608 --> 17:26.915
I made my own lunches,

17:27.002 --> 17:28.699
I hitchhiked to school.

17:28.786 --> 17:30.527
What's that got to do with

17:30.614 --> 17:33.313
you being a bitter, angry,
resentful woman right now?

17:35.924 --> 17:38.883
I said this is not
a conversation!

17:43.584 --> 17:44.324
[deep voice]:
Hey, dude.

17:44.411 --> 17:46.717
Pass the joy.

17:48.850 --> 17:50.112
I don't have it.

17:50.199 --> 17:52.158
I don't have it, either.

17:54.116 --> 17:55.509
[chuckles]

17:55.596 --> 17:58.381
Too bad it's not a phone.
We could call it.

17:58.468 --> 17:59.861
[laughing]

17:59.948 --> 18:00.862
Whoa.

18:00.949 --> 18:03.082
What?

18:04.126 --> 18:05.954
This is amazing weed.

18:06.041 --> 18:07.912
I can see your farts!

18:11.916 --> 18:16.182
Awesome.

18:16.269 --> 18:18.053
Do you honestly believe
you have to remind me

18:18.140 --> 18:20.186
how much I screwed up?

18:20.273 --> 18:21.578
You don't think
I carry that with me

18:21.665 --> 18:23.537
every minute
of every freaking day?

18:23.624 --> 18:24.581
Do you?

18:24.668 --> 18:25.408
The actual amount of time

18:25.495 --> 18:27.018
is not important.

18:28.759 --> 18:30.239
All you need to know

18:30.326 --> 18:32.111
is I am trying to be here
for you right now,

18:32.198 --> 18:34.852
and you can stop beating me up
for who I used to be,

18:34.939 --> 18:36.027
because I've got that covered.

18:39.596 --> 18:41.294
But I like beating you up.

18:44.949 --> 18:46.342
How's this for a plan?

18:46.429 --> 18:48.736
You can blame me
for all your problems

18:48.823 --> 18:51.434
on Tuesdays, Thursdays
and Sundays.

18:51.521 --> 18:53.871
I'll punish myself
the rest of the week.

18:56.135 --> 18:57.353
Well, it is Monday.

18:59.007 --> 19:00.748
All right.

19:00.835 --> 19:03.229
I was a terrible mother.

19:03.316 --> 19:04.665
And I let you down,

19:04.752 --> 19:07.711
and nobody hates me
more than me.

19:07.798 --> 19:09.539
How's that?

19:12.238 --> 19:14.414
It would've been better
if you cried.

19:16.851 --> 19:18.853
I'll work on it.

19:21.943 --> 19:23.205
I'm so sorry, baby.

19:26.077 --> 19:27.078
Aw...

19:31.082 --> 19:33.172
Do you smell something?

19:35.130 --> 19:38.220
[deep voice]:
Uh-oh.

19:42.224 --> 19:45.184
You were so smart
to save this.

19:46.402 --> 19:47.447
Thanks.

19:47.534 --> 19:49.623
It's the herbal tea, right?

19:49.710 --> 19:51.059
As you requested.

19:51.146 --> 19:52.452
Just checking.

19:57.196 --> 19:59.981
Purple's such
a pretty color.

20:00.068 --> 20:01.417
It doesn't
feel pretty.

20:05.160 --> 20:08.250
I do love taking
care of you.

20:08.337 --> 20:10.426
I love it, too, Mom.

20:10.513 --> 20:11.688
Well... probably
should've done it

20:11.775 --> 20:12.646
when you were a kid.

20:12.733 --> 20:14.169
That would've been nice.

20:18.129 --> 20:20.131
[thunder rumbles]

20:22.612 --> 20:24.223
[exhales]
Gotta hand it Baxter.

20:24.310 --> 20:26.660
He did a good
job up there.

20:26.747 --> 20:28.009
Yeah, he did.

20:28.096 --> 20:29.837
I'm hard on him, but...

20:29.924 --> 20:31.055
he is trying
to step up.

20:31.142 --> 20:33.144
Maybe people can change.

20:33.232 --> 20:35.669
[water drips]

20:38.715 --> 20:40.674
Or maybe not.

20:42.197 --> 20:43.503
[pops lips]

20:43.590 --> 20:44.982
If it makes you
feel any better,

20:45.069 --> 20:46.332
I forgot you wanted herbal.

